    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-salt-and-pepper-pork-with-sesame-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Combine your<strong> cornflour </strong>and<strong> </strong>2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>with your <strong>five-spice mix </strong>(not a fan of five-spice? Just add a little!)<strong> </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>pork strips</strong> and give everything a good mix up until well coated \u2013 these are your <strong>coated pork strips</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-salt-and-pepper-pork-with-sesame-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated pork strips</strong></p><p>Cook for 7-8 min, turning once half-way, or until the pork is crispy and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>pork</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-salt-and-pepper-pork-with-sesame-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pork is cooking, trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> on the diagonal</p><p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es] </strong>finely on the diagonal</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-salt-and-pepper-pork-with-sesame-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es] of <strong>cooked long grain rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave </strong>for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-salt-and-pepper-pork-with-sesame-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is crispy, add the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> and <strong>chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min or until very fragrant \u2013 this is your <strong>salt & pepper pork</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-salt-and-pepper-pork-with-sesame-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is piping hot, transfer the <strong>cooked rice</strong> to a heatproof bowl with your <strong>blanched peas </strong>and the<strong> remaining sesame oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-salt-and-pepper-pork-with-sesame-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>salt & pepper pork </strong>with the <strong>sesame rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
